#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:200
msgid "Registering payments"
msgstr "Registering payments"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:202
msgid ""
"To register vendor payments made with SCT, first verify that "
"an :guilabel:`Account Number` and :guilabel:`Bank` are indicated on the "
"vendor's :doc:`contact form <../../../essentials/contacts>`, under "
"the :guilabel:`Accounting` tab. Odoo automatically verifies if the IBAN "
"format is respected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:206
msgid ""
"Then, go to :menuselection:`Vendors --> Payments`, and "
"click :guilabel:`New`. When creating your payment, select :guilabel:`SEPA "
"Credit Transfer` as the :guilabel:`Payment Method`. The :guilabel:`Vendor "
"Bank Account` is automatically populated based on the :guilabel:`Vendor` "
"selected. For future payments to this vendor, Odoo will automatically "
"suggest the bank account, but it remains possible to select a new one from "
"the dropdown menu by clicking the :guilabel:`Vendor Bank Account` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:213
msgid ""
"Once your payment is registered, do not forget to confirm it. You can also "
"pay vendor bills from the bill directly using the :guilabel:`Register "
"Payment` button at the top of a vendor bill. The form is the same, but the "
"payment is directly linked to the bill and will be automatically reconciled "
"with it."
msgstr ""
"Once your payment is registered, do not forget to confirm it. You can also "
"pay vendor bills from the bill directly using the :guilabel:`Register "
"Payment` button at the top of a vendor bill. The form is the same, but the "
"payment is directly linked to the bill and will be automatically reconciled "
"with it."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:221
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:148
msgid "ISO 20022"
msgstr "ISO 20022"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:223
msgid ""
"ISO 20022 is a global standard for the exchange of payment data between "
"banks. It uses a format that lets payment details and related documents move "
"together as a single package. This means information such as invoice "
"numbers, tax details, and who sent the payment is stored in fields that "
"computers can automatically read. Unlike SEPA, the ISO 20022 standard can be "
"used with any currency worldwide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:228
msgid ""
"In Odoo, the SEPA Payments module acts as the underlying engine for all ISO "
"20022 transactions (both domestic SEPA payments in euros and non-euro global "
"transfers are supported by the module)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:231
msgid ""
":doc:`Some countries and regions <sepa_payments>` may use a localized, "
"country-specific version of ISO 20022, which requires additional "
"configuration. In these cases, we strongly recommend reading the :ref:`PAIN "
"version <accounting/sepa_payments/pain>` section of this page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:238
msgid "PAIN version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:241
msgid ""
":abbr:`PAIN (PAyment INitiation)` is the specific message protocol within "
"ISO 20022 used to send transfer instructions from Odoo to your bank."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:243
msgid ""
"To enable a country-specific PAIN version, first check that you have "
"the :doc:`fiscal localization <../../../finance/fiscal_localizations>` for "
"your country installed in your database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:248
msgid ""
"ISO 20022 **PAIN.001.001.03** is being deprecated in November 2026. Make "
"sure to use the newer **PAIN.001.001.09** version or the one required in "
"your country."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/sepa_payments.rst:251
msgid ""
"To select a specific PAIN version, open the **Accounting** app, go "
"to :menuselection:`Configuration --> Journals`, and open "
"your :guilabel:`Bank` journal. Click the :guilabel:`Outgoing Payments` tab, "
